Stoke Extinguisher is an upcoming EP by NOFX. It is scheduled to be released on November 26, 2013 through Fat Wreck Chords. The EP will be released as a six-song CD and a two-song 7". Both versions feature the new title song, "Stoke Extinguisher", as well as "The Shortest Pier", which was originally by Tony Sly and was recorded for The Songs of Tony Sly: A Tribute. The rest of the songs on the CD are b-sides collected from singles from the band's most recent album, Self Entitled. The cover was hand painted by Jason Cruz of Strung Out.
